This paper deals with the application of Optimality Theory, a linguistic theory, to computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of gradient constraints, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also involves the use of finite-state methods, which are commonly used in automata theory and formal languages, making cs.SD (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with syllabification analysis, which is a topic in phonology, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a possible category as well.
